<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:194px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:153.61%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/ShadowOfTheWindCover_6293.JPG" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/ShadowOfTheWindCover_6293.JPG" width="194" height="298"></div></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p><em>The Shadow of the Wind</em> is a 2001 best-selling mystery novel by Spanish author Carlos Ruiz Zaf&oacute;n.</p><p>Set in Barcelona after the Spanish Civil War, the story follows Daniel, who, as a young boy, discovers a long-forgotten book in a secret library entitled <em>The Shadow of the Wind</em> by Juli&aacute;n Carax. Daniel tries to seek out other books by the author, but can find nothing and no information on Carax himself. Then he hears stories of a strange man calling himself Lain Coubert, the name of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Satan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Satan">devil</a> in Carax's book, who is seeking out and burning all copies of the mysterious author's novels.</p><p></p><hr><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><h2>This book contains examples of:</h2><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlliterativeName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlliterativeName">Alliterative Name</a>: Miquel Moliner.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimalMotifs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimalMotifs">Animal Motifs</a>: Fumero is associated with insects: cold, calculating, heartless.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeButImpractical" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AwesomeButImpractical">Awesome, but Impractical</a>: Tom&aacute;s Aguilar devotes his time to building things like the "aerostatic dart." Daniel points this out.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BabiesEverAfter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BabiesEverAfter">Babies Ever After</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Daniel and Bea's son. Ferm&iacute;n as well ended with four kids.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeenThereShapedHistory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeenThereShapedHistory">Been There, Shaped History</a>: Fructu&oacute;s Gelabert was a pioneering film maker from Barcelona that made what is considered the first Spanish movie with a plot. Apparently he funded this by getting paid by eccentric millionaire Jaus&agrave; in exchange of filming his mansion <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext">so he can catch the spirit of his cuban lover</a>, and when he disapears, by a huge check from Mr. Aldaya to never mention the matter again.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater">Big Eater</a>: Ferm&iacute;n, despite being described as underweight, has an incredible appetite.</li><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BleakAbyssRetirementHome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BleakAbyssRetirementHome">Bleak Abyss Retirement Home</a>: Santa Lucia's Asylum. Where all the old homless (and sometimes mad) people of Barcelona end.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookEnds" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookEnds">Book-Ends</a>: A Zaf&oacute;n trademark, along with the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstPersonSmartass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstPersonSmartass">First-Person Smartass</a> narrative.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BroodingBoyGentleGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BroodingBoyGentleGirl">Brooding Boy, Gentle Girl</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n and Nuria's friendship has shades of this, particularly their time together in France</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrotherSisterIncest" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrotherSisterIncest">Brother&#150;Sister Incest</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Juli&aacute;n and Pen&eacute;lope fall in love, but they turn out to be half-siblings from their father's side</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGun">Chekhov's Gun</a>:<ul><li> The Montblanc Pen Daniel gets as a birthday present on his sixteenth birthday.</li><li> The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProductPlacement" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProductPlacement">Sugus candy</a> that Ferm&iacute;n gives Daniel to calm him down.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGunman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGunman">Chekhov's Gunman</a>:<ul><li> Ferm&iacute;n himself is introduced just as a homeless man asking Daniel to let him enter the house to avoid the rain. And then helping him after he is beaten up. He ended being hired by Daniel's father in the following chapters.</li><li> In one chapter Daniel recounts how he met his friend Tom&aacute;s when Daniel insulted his sister Beatriz and Tom&aacute;s punched him. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> She ended having a larger role on the story than her brother, ending as Daniel's romantic interest and eventual wife.</span></li><li> While Daniel and Ferm&iacute;n where investigating, they stopped in a restaurant where a man was impressed by how much Ferm&iacute;n could eat, and was then seen on their way back in the train laughing at Ferm&iacute;n discussing with some nuns. He turned out to be <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> one of Fumero's henchmen, Palacios, that was following them.</span></li><li> Fumero might be considered a retroactive one. When he first introduces himself, he shows his ID that gives his full name as <em>Francisco Javier Fumero Almu&ntilde;iz</em>. So if you pay attention <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> you might not be taken by surprise that one of Julian former school friends was named Javier</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColdBloodedTorture" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColdBloodedTorture">Cold-Blooded Torture</a>: Ferm&iacute;n is covered in scars that are revealed to be the result of this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyChild" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyChild">Creepy Child</a>: Inspector Fumero, naturally, who used to capture cats and pigeons and torture them for hours. Juli&aacute;n was a milder version.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathByChildbirth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathByChildbirth">Death by Childbirth</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n's lover dies in childbirth</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeliberateValuesDissonance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeliberateValuesDissonance">Deliberate Values Dissonance</a>: The casual mistreatment of women which was true during the fifties in Spain. One older (and even more dissonant) woman talking about Julian's dad says that while she understand that a man must hit his wife sometimes for her to obey him, he just hit her out of nowhere.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon">Despair Event Horizon</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n, after finding out that Pen&eacute;lope died, even worse is that she died with their child as the gravestone marks</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DevelopmentHell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DevelopmentHell">Development Hell</a>: In-Universe. Master Neri, Clara's Piano teacher, has been composing a symphony for some time. It remained in that stage during all the years that Daniel visited Clara. Ten years after the story, we are told he is still working on it.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisabledLoveInterest" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisabledLoveInterest">Disabled Love Interest</a>: Clara, Gustavo Barcelo's blind niece, was the object of Daniel's teenaged affections.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DrivenToSuicide" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DrivenToSuicide">Driven to Suicide</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Mr. Aldaya decided to jump from his ship and being eaten by sharks on his way to Argentina.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarnYourHappyEnding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarnYourHappyEnding">Earn Your Happy Ending</a>:<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Daniel ends with a caring wife and a lovely child ten years after the story. And he only needed to be beaten up twice, scared by a weird man, being threatened by the goverment, and be shot to get it.</span></li><li> Even <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Juli&aacute;n gets his will to live restored by Daniel, and gets to start writing again</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneWentToSchoolTogether" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneWentToSchoolTogether">Everyone Went to School Together</a>: When Daniel and Ferm&iacute;n goes to San Gabriel to look into Julian's past, the first priest they encounter there happens to be a former friend of him. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> And they were also friends with Fumero.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakeNationality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakeNationality">Fake Nationality</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>. At one point before the story, Ferm&iacute;n presents himself as being Cuban.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForeignCultureFetish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForeignCultureFetish">Foreign Culture Fetish</a>: Barcel&oacute; is an great admirer of the XIX century, to the point of dressing in the old-fashioned style and using a monocle and pipe, both for show.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice">Framing Device</a>: A significant part of Juli&aacute;n and Miquel's story is told through Nuria's letter to Daniel (which was sent <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> after she was murdered</span>.)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FreudianExcuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FreudianExcuse">Freudian Excuse</a>: Literally: according to Miquel, Fumero told him that his mother abused him sexually, which in his opinion may explain everything which came after.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FullNameBasis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FullNameBasis">Full-Name Basis</a>: Ferm&iacute;n Romero de Torres. When Daniel mentions him, nine out of ten would be by his full name.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GeniusBruiser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GeniusBruiser">Genius Bruiser</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GentleGiant" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GentleGiant">Gentle Giant</a>: Both apply to Tom&aacute;s Aguilar</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiveMeASword" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiveMeASword">Give Me a Sword</a>: In the final fight Fumero lost his gun during a fight with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Julian</span> and couldn't find it when he got the upper hand. So he ordered his subordinate Palacios to hand him his gun. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> But he refused.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HappilyMarried" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HappilyMarried">Happily Married</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> both Daniel and Ferm&iacute;n ended like this with their respective interests</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn">Heel&#150;Face Turn</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Palacios refusing to give his gun to Fumero for killing Daniel.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroesWantRedheads" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroesWantRedheads">Heroes Want Redheads</a>: Daniel for <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Beatriz</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBastard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBastard">Heroic Bastard</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n Carax was Ricardo Aldaya's son (and therefore Jorge and Pen&eacute;lope's half-brother)</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice">Heroic Sacrifice</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Miquel Moliner</span> sacrifices himself for Juli&aacute;n by pretending to be him and shooting two police officers.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeterosexualLifePartners" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeterosexualLifePartners">Heterosexual Life-Partners</a>: Miquel and Juli&aacute;n seemed to be this, although it's more apparent on Miquel's side.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HighClassGlass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HighClassGlass">High-Class Glass</a>: Barcel&oacute;, as part of his admiration for the XIX century.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HistoricalDomainCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HistoricalDomainCharacter">Historical Domain Character</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/FranciscoFranco" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/FranciscoFranco">Franco's</a> shadow can be felt <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreaterScopeVillain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreaterScopeVillain">all over the book</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HookerWithAHeartOfGold" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HookerWithAHeartOfGold">Hooker with a Heart of Gold</a>: Roci&iacute;to proves to be one at the end of the story.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HospitalEpilogue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HospitalEpilogue">Hospital Epilogue</a>: The last chapter of the book. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Everyone is at the hospital visiting Daniel after he needed to be revived.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveManyNames" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveManyNames">I Have Many Names</a>: Ferm&iacute;n. We know that that's not his name. And Fumero at one point calls him his "friend of the thousand names."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IfYouEverDoAnythingToHurtHer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IfYouEverDoAnythingToHurtHer">If You Ever Do Anything to Hurt Her...</a>: Daniel gets one from <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Tom&aacute;s when he starts seeing his sister.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InadequateInheritor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InadequateInheritor">Inadequate Inheritor</a>: A common theme on the book.<ul><li> Don Ricardo thought his son Jorge didn't had the character to succeed him, which drove him to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">search for his illegitimate son, Juli&aacute;n</span>.</li><li> Mr Aguilar actually instructed Tom&aacute;s' tutors to act as if he were stupid.</li><li> This is just one of the many layers of friction between Don Antoni and his son Juli&aacute;n.</li><li> When the Aldayas' fortune began to go down, some people believed that Don Ricardo was just an idiot that wasted what his father founded.</li><li> Nuria's former boss, Cabestany, said that his son would bankrupt his Publisher House in six months after his death. She said he was really optimistic, it took two months.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InformedAttractiveness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InformedAttractiveness">Informed Attractiveness</a>: Nuria is described many times throughout the novel as very attractive, even in her older years; she is even hit on and sexually harassed by her crooked new boss.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IOweYouMyLife" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IOweYouMyLife">I Owe You My Life</a>: Ferm&iacute;n will do anything he can for Daniel and his father as they have taken him in from the street and gave him a job, making him a respectable citizen again.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JekyllAndHyde" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JekyllAndHyde">Jekyll &amp; Hyde</a>: A variant with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n Carax,</span> who, after his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DespairEventHorizon">Despair Event Horizon</a>, takes on the name of La&iacute;n Coubert, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> a character he himself created.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LadykillerInLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LadykillerInLove">Ladykiller in Love</a>: Ferm&iacute;n to Bernarda.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawOfInverseFertility" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawOfInverseFertility">Law of Inverse Fertility</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n gets Penelope pregnant the first time they have sex, same goes for Daniel and Bea</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLostLenore" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLostLenore">The Lost Lenore</a>: Pen&eacute;lope, for Juli&aacute;n.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMakesYouEvil">Love Makes You Evil</a>: Fumero first attempt to murder someone was inspired by unrequited love.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMartyr" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveMartyr">Love Martyr</a>: Nuria Monfort for <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n Carax,</span> especially after his transformation into La&iacute;n Coubert. It doesn't work.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadeOfIron" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadeOfIron">Made of Iron</a>:<ul><li> Ferm&iacute;n, who, after being severely beaten by Inspector Fumero, recovers rapidly and immediately starts groping the nurse.</li><li> Also <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n Carax,</span> who survives having all his skin burnt off.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicalRealism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicalRealism">Magical Realism</a>: Aldaya's house is haunted but nothing comes out of it.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Malaproper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Malaproper">Malaproper</a>:<ul><li> La Bernarda. She believes that Barcel&oacute;'s agnosticism is some kind of illness in his throat.</li><li> When Ferm&iacute;n explains to Roci&iacute;to that he hasn't "visited" her as frequently is because of monogamy. She responds that maybe some penicillin might help with that.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulEcho" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulEcho">Meaningful Echo</a>:<ul><li> "The day I die, all that was once mine will be yours..." "...except your dreams." Between <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n and Miquel, both as children, and then moments before Miquel dies.</span></li><li> And again between Daniel and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> his son,</span> at the end of the book, mirroring the very first chapter.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MindScrew" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MindScrew">Mind Screw</a>: Thanks to multiple <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Reveal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Reveal">Reveals</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JigsawPuzzlePlot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JigsawPuzzlePlot">that leave out some important particular.</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAppeal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAppeal">Zaf&oacute;n does it with</a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAppeal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAppeal">every single novel</a></em> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAppeal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAppeal">he writes.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorMonster">Mirror Monster</a>: As a child, Juli&aacute;n made up stories that he had a sister who lived in hell and came to visit him through the mirror.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityChain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityChain">Morality Chain</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> When Juli&aacute;n finds out Pen&eacute;lope died years ago, his world falls apart and he starts burning his own books.</span> Until Daniel appears in his life.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityPet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityPet">Morality Pet</a>: Daniel to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n</span> who sees himself and another chance at life in him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderTheHypotenuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderTheHypotenuse">Murder the Hypotenuse</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Fumero <em>tried</em> to do this to Juli&aacute;n.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown">No-Holds-Barred Beatdown</a>: Daniel ended in the end of two of these. Ferm&iacute;n also got one from Fumero.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoNameGiven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoNameGiven">No Name Given</a>: Ferm&iacute;n Romero de Torres is an alias, of course. We never do find out his real name. A newspaper in the novel gives his name as Antonio Jos&eacute; Guti&eacute;rrez Alcayete. Given the newspaper gets his informations from Fumero, it could actually be the real one - in fact, the article bills the guy named Alcayete from C&aacute;ceres, Extremadura, which is precisely the place Ferm&iacute;n himself mentions later as his native town.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NouveauRiche" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NouveauRiche">Nouveau Riche</a>: The industrial period.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlotParallel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlotParallel">Plot Parallel</a>: There are plenty of parallels between the stories of Juli&aacute;n and Daniel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PosthumousCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PosthumousCharacter">Posthumous Character</a>: Guess who? <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Subverted with Juli&aacute;n, who turns out to be still alive. Nuria Monfort is a straighter example. And also Miquel</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrimalScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrimalScene">Primal Scene</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Daniel, wanting to make sure that Clara is safe, ended interrupting one of her "classes" with master Neri. This earns Daniel his first beatdown of the book.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReallyGetsAround" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReallyGetsAround">Really Gets Around</a>: Ferm&iacute;n is a mild version of this, he flirts with every woman he sees, but has stayed monogamous since he met Bernarda.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReveal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheReveal">The Reveal</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> the identity of La&igrave;n Coubert is quite shocking, especially after the author spent most of the book trying to make the reader think it was Jorge Aldaya.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RomanticFalseLead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RomanticFalseLead">Romantic False Lead</a>: Clara is introduced as Daniel's love interest in the story, but after the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrimalScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrimalScene">Primal Scene</a> she pretty much disappears from the story, only making a couple of brief appearances.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoomFullOfCrazy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoomFullOfCrazy">Room Full of Crazy</a>: Juli&aacute;n's childhood room is covered in crosses and Catholic symbols, though it's his father, not him, who did it.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag">Running Gag</a>: Any drink that Ferm&iacute;n prepares tastes like diesel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShipperOnDeck" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShipperOnDeck">Shipper on Deck</a>: Both Ferm&iacute;n and Mr. Sempere are really glad of Daniel's "date" with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Bea.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a>: Barcel&oacute; referenced <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/Pygmalion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/Pygmalion">Pygmalion</a> when he hired Bernarda. Even stating that she would be his Eliza, and he would be her Prof. Higgings.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnowMeansDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnowMeansDeath">Snow Means Death</a>: During the last part of the story a strange snowstorm hits Barcelona out of nowhere. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> And is during this storm that both Daniel and Fumero died. (But Daniel gets better).</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StalkerWithACrush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StalkerWithACrush">Stalker with a Crush</a>: Francisco Javier Fumero used to be one for <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Pen&eacute;lope Aldaya</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StarCrossedLovers" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StarCrossedLovers">Star-Crossed Lovers</a>:<ul><li> Juli&aacute;n and Pen&eacute;lope fall in love with each other, but they only get one night together before he is forced to flee Barcelona because of the wrath of her father, in the end she dies at childbirth.</li><li> Daniel and Bea, since she is set to marry a soldier as soon as he returns from service, despite their growing feelings for each other, and the disapproval of her father for Daniel. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope">Subverted Trope</a> as at the end Daniel and Bea do get married</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrangeMindsThinkAlike" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StrangeMindsThinkAlike">Strange Minds Think Alike</a>: Daniel says that finding <em>The Shadow of the Wind</em> in the cemetery felt like the book was actually waiting for him since before he was even born. When <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Beatriz</span> chooses a book to take out, she says the exact same thing.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SurpriseIncest" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SurpriseIncest">Surprise Incest</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Juli&aacute;n doesn't know that Pen&eacute;lope is his half-sister</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThatManIsDead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThatManIsDead">That Man Is Dead</a>:<ul><li> Late in the book we confirm that Ferm&iacute;n Romero de Torres is not the man's real name. But he confesses to Daniel that it might as well be now, saying that the other man was tortured to death in Montj&uuml;ic.</li><li> Lain Coubert character has shades of this as well. Not only he doesn't want to remember anything about his previous life, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> but wants to erase it as well by burning his books.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TragicMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TragicMonster">Tragic Monster</a>: La&iacute;n Coubert.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainWithGoodPublicity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainWithGoodPublicity">Villain with Good Publicity</a>: Again, Fumero, who always seems to be on the winning side.<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> He falls from grace as he dies and his plaque is now hidden behind the soda machine at the police station</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine">Wham Line</a>:<ul><li> "In seven days <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> I will be dead.</span>"</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> "Juli&aacute;n and Pen&eacute;lope are siblings."</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeUsedToBeFriends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeUsedToBeFriends">We Used to Be Friends</a>:<ul><li> Jorge Aldaya and Juli&aacute;n used to be best friends in school, but after the latter flees Barcelona after his affair with Pen&eacute;lope, Jorge's sister, is discovered, they loose all contact; then after his family's name falls into ruin, Jorge's father makes him swear to kill Juli&aacute;n to avenge their family.</li><li> Mirroring the above example, Dani&eacute;l and Tom&aacute;s are best friends until the former gets involved with the latter's sister, Bea; by the end of the book their friendship has been damaged and Tom&aacute;s goes on to live in Germany, never speaking with Dani&eacute;l again.</li></ul></li></ul><hr>
</div>
